.TH CLAUDE-CTX 1 "2025-11-12" "claude-ctx 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
claude-ctx \- Manage Claude CTX agents, skills, workflows, and the interactive TUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claude-ctx
[B-hR | B--helpR]
.br
.B claude-ctx
ICOMMANDR [ISUBCOMMANDR] [IARGSR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claude-ctx
is the command-line entry point for the Claude CTX plugin. It lets you inspect and
activate agents, modes, and rules, launch curated workflows, orchestrate scenarios,
export context bundles, and open the Rich/Textual-based TUI for day-to-day
operations. The CLI reads the Claude context tree from
.BR CLAUDE_CTX_HOME ,
.BR CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT ,
then B~/.claudeR (first match wins).

Many commands expose additional help with
.B --help
on the command or subcommand.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR -h \, --help
Show help for the current command and exit.
.SH COMMAND SUMMARY
.TP
.B status
Display overall health: active agents, modes, rules, workflows, and metrics.
.TP
.B mode
List, activate, or deactivate behavioral modes.
.TP
.B agent
Inspect, activate, deactivate, or validate agents plus dependency graphs.
.TP
.B rules
Manage rule modules that enforce workflow, quality, or efficiency policies.
.TP
.B skills
List, inspect, validate, and analyze skills plus community registry operations.
.TP
.B profile
Save, list, or load multi-agent profiles (built-in or custom snapshots).
.TP
.B init
Bootstrap a repository with wizard-driven defaults or cached state.
.TP
.B workflow
Run, list, resume, stop, or monitor predefined multi-step workflows.
.TP
.B orchestrate
Preview, validate, run, or stop YAML scenarios (alias: BorchR).
See Bclaude-ctx-workflowR(1) for workflow + scenario details.
.TP
.B mcp
Inspect or validate Model Context Protocol servers.
.TP
.B ai
Show recommendations, auto-activate confident agents, export metrics, or record
feedback for the intelligent assistant.
.TP
.B export
List exportable components and emit Markdown bundles or stdout streams.
.TP
.B tui
Launch the interactive dashboard. See Bclaude-ctx-tuiR(1).
