.SH FILES
The CLI reads and writes inside the Claude home directory (default: B~/.claudeR).
Key paths include:
.TP
.B ~/.claude/agents/
Agent definitions and metadata.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/modes/
Active mode definitions. Inactive modes live under inactive/modes/R.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/rules/
Reusable rule modules.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/skills/
Skill definitions, dependency maps, metric ledgers, and community registries.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/workflows/
Workflow YAML definitions.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/scenarios/
Scenario orchestration definitions.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/profiles/
Saved profile snapshots.
.TP
.B ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md
Primary include file loaded by Claude Code.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDE_CTX_HOME
Override the location of the Claude context tree.
.TP
.B CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT
Alternative override (set automatically inside Claude Code).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Activate a debugging mode:
.nf
claude-ctx mode activate debug
.fi
.TP
Toggle an agent stack and inspect dependencies:
.nf
claude-ctx agent activate python-expert reviewer
claude-ctx agent deps python-expert
.fi
.TP
Validate everything before a release:
.nf
claude-ctx agent validate --all
claude-ctx skills validate --all
claude-ctx orchestrate validate --all
.fi
.TP
Generate workflow and scenario output:
.nf
claude-ctx workflow run feature-development
claude-ctx orchestrate run launch-day --plan
.fi
.TP
Stop the active workflow before switching tasks:
.nf
claude-ctx workflow stop feature-development
.fi
.TP
Export a trimmed context bundle:
.nf
claude-ctx export context release-notes.md \
    --exclude-category agents \
    --exclude-file "rules/experimental-rules.md"
.fi
